# 🧠 🔥 How many “gateways” should you know?

👉 Don’t try to memorize everything randomly.
👉 Focus on **5 CORE gateways** (these cover 90% of interviews)

---

# 🚀 ✅ 5 MUST-KNOW GATEWAYS

---

## 🔵 1. Internet Gateway (IGW)

![Image](https://miro.medium.com/1%2Agftv4LSqU_12kRqNwYISJw.png)

![Image](https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width%3D800%2Cheight%3D%2Cfit%3Dscale-down%2Cgravity%3Dauto%2Cformat%3Dauto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fe87kfori55y64rlgzfii.png)

![Image](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/images/vpc/latest/userguide/images/vpc-bpa-4.png)

![Image](https://miro.medium.com/1%2AE1DPFA0XyDhyRGTfELGpBQ.png)

👉 Purpose:

```text
Connect VPC to internet
```

👉 Key points:

* Supports **inbound + outbound**
* Used in **public subnet**

---

## 🔵 2. NAT Gateway

![Image](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/images/vpc/latest/userguide/images/public-nat-gateway-diagram.png)

![Image](https://miro.medium.com/1%2Agftv4LSqU_12kRqNwYISJw.png)

![Image](https://guides.zadarastorage.com/cs-networking-guide/latest/_images/02-NAT-Gateway-Overview_Symphony-1024x797.png)

![Image](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/images/vpc/latest/userguide/images/nat-instance_updated.png)

👉 Purpose:

```text
Allow private subnet → internet (outbound only)
```

👉 Key points:

* ❌ No inbound
* ✔ Only outbound

---

## 🔵 3. Virtual Private Gateway (VGW)

👉 Purpose:

```text
AWS side of Site-to-Site VPN
```

👉 Used when:

* Connecting office → AWS

---

## 🔵 4. Transit Gateway (TGW)

👉 Purpose:

```text
Connect multiple VPCs + VPN centrally
```

👉 Think:

```text
Network hub
```

---

## 🔵 5. VPC Peering (not gateway but MUST KNOW)

👉 Purpose:

```text
Direct connection between 2 VPCs
```

👉 Used for:

* Small setups

---

# 🧠 🔥 Bonus (Know at high level)

---

## 🟡 6. Customer Gateway (CGW)

👉 Your office router
👉 Needed for VPN

---

## 🟡 7. Egress-Only Internet Gateway

👉 For:

```text
IPv6 outbound only
```

👉 Rarely asked

---

## 🟡 8. Gateway Load Balancer

👉 Advanced:

* For firewalls

👉 Skip for now

---

# 🧠 🔥 How to remember (SUPER SIMPLE)

---

## 🌐 Internet access

```text
IGW → public subnet
NAT → private subnet
```

---

## 🔐 Hybrid (VPN)

```text
VGW → AWS side
CGW → office side
```

---

## 🔗 Multi-network

```text
Peering → small scale
Transit Gateway → large scale
```

---

# 🎯 Interview Cheat Sheet

```text
IGW  → internet access (public)
NAT  → internet access (private outbound)
VGW  → VPN entry point
TGW  → connect many VPCs
Peering → connect 2 VPCs
```

---

# 💪 What YOU should focus on

---

## ✅ MUST MASTER (for your level)

* IGW ✔
* NAT Gateway ✔
* VGW (VPN) ✔
* Transit Gateway (basic understanding) ✔

---

## ⚠️ OPTIONAL

* Egress-only IGW
* Gateway Load Balancer

---

# 🚀 Final Answer

👉 You should **strongly know 4–5 gateways**:

> **IGW, NAT Gateway, Virtual Private Gateway, Transit Gateway (+ VPC Peering)**

👉 That’s enough for **most interviews**

